Class RegistryEntry<T extends IRegistryEntry<T>>

    Adventure, Entity, ModItemTest, Tile

    public abstract class RegistryEntry<T extends IRegistryEntry<T>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements IRegistryEntry<T>
    An abstract RegistryEntry. Contains concrete implementations of the methods in IRegistryEntry. Unless you think that my methods are deeply flawed in some way, best practise is to extend this class if you want to create a new registerable type.

      • setIdentifier

        public void setIdentifier(Identifier identifier)
        Description copied from interface: IRegistryEntry
        Sets the identifier of this IRegistryEntry. If called more than once, should throw an Exception.

        Should only be called once during initialisation. Modders should never need to call this, as this will be handled during registration by the VoltsOfDoomCoreSystem. The exception to this is if you are writing your own registry system completely disregarding the built in system.
        Specified by:
